<div><br><span style="font-size: small;"><strong>4. Adding Time</strong></span></div>
<div><br><span style="font-size: small;">Here is a nice simple way to add hours and minutes together:</span><br><span style="font-size: small;">Let's add 1 hr and 35 minutes and 3 hr 55 minutes together.</span><br><span style="font-size: small;">What you do is this:</span><br><span style="font-size: small;">make the 1 hr 35 minutes into one number, which will give us 135 and do</span><br><span style="font-size: small;">the same for the other number, 3 hours 55 minutes, giving us 355</span><br><span style="font-size: small;">Now you want to add these two numbers together:</span><br><span style="font-size: small;">135</span><br><span style="font-size: small;">355</span><br><span style="font-size: small;">___ </span><br><span style="font-size: small;">490</span><br><span style="font-size: small;">So we now have a sub total of 490.</span><br><span style="font-size: small;">What you need to do to this and all sub totals is</span><br><span style="font-size: small;">add the time constant of 40.</span><br><span style="font-size: small;">No matter what the hours and minutes are,</span><br><span style="font-size: small;">just add the 40 time constant to the sub total.</span><br><span style="font-size: small;">490 + 40 = 530</span><br><span style="font-size: small;">So we can now see our answer is 5 hrs and 30 minutes!</span></div>
